text:
Bad Service.  Ramen Noodle served too dry.

When i asked add more soup, the waitress rejected add more soup just because she said already give soup at my noodle

While the noodles looked like the ones you find at the other Ippudo chains, the bite is missing and overall texture is different. Pretty disappointing given that itâ€™s quite pricey. Portion is also seems much smaller.

Part of the renowned ippudo chain, it offers made to order ramen within the transit area. However, the menu is extremely limited and it is not exactly cheap considering how tiny the portions are. While it is comforting food, if you are looking for a substantial meal, probably best to go elsewhere
The ramen served here is quite affordable and the noodle still palatable, nonetheless the lack of proper bowl and the  quality of the side dishes still remain a lot to be desired.
Compared with price of other,  this is ok.  But they close early.  Check the office hour first.  Not much people eating.
